main event: Two civilian observers reported seeing a single luminous object in the sky that moved in an 'oscillating' manner. The object was not detected on radar.
interesting points: The object was described as being the same intensity as the North Star and appeared starlike.
One of the observers, a military sergeant, called the Space Detection and Tracking Center and was told that the satellite Echo I was passing through the area at the time.
The sergeant was able to distinguish the difference between the satellite and the unidentified object.
In the opinion of the sergeant, the object was likely a star whose apparent movement was caused by a temperature inversion.
The investigating officer concurred with the sergeant's analysis that the object was probably a star.
